23.1 Version of Operating System

23.2 


?.1	Hard Disk - Partition Editor

?.2	Hard Disk - Health
	- boot from network
	- double-click Testools
	- click Parted Magic
	- choose 64 bit
	- click Disk Health
	- select disk drive
	- click Attributes tab
	- check if the following:
		# 5   Raw value
		# 7   raw value
		# 196 raw value

?.3	Hard Disk - Erase
	- boot from network
	- double-click Testools
	- click Parted Magic
 	- choose 64 bit
	- choose Erase Disk
	- choose Internal
	- choose ATA Secure Erase button
	- check if 'Frozen' is displayed
	- choose Sleep
	  - the laptop will automatically power off
	  - power on the laptop as soon as the power goes off
	- check if 'Not Frozen' replaced 'Frozen'
	- click checkbox for /dev/sda
	- click Continue button
	- click checkbox for 'I allow .....'
	- click Start button
	  - the duration time will be displayed (usually about 90 minutes or 		more)

?.1	Battery - Capacity Check
	- command line: upower -d | less
	- check if capacity is 100%
	- get capacity if it is not 100%
		Formula:  Energy-full divided by energy-full design 				multiplied by 100
	
?.2	Battery - Charging
	- power chord on
	- check if battery is charging
	- if it is not charging, replace the battery with one that is 		charging


?.1	Power On - Power Source
	- check if laptop powers on battery alone
		- replace battery with one 
	- check if laptop powers on from power chord
	- check if laptop posers on, on both battery and power chord 

?.2	Power On - Potential Issue
	- Pop up message 'System program problem detected'
	- Solution:  Enter the following on the command line
	- Command line: sudo rm /var/crash/*

?.3  	Power On - Reboot on command line
	- Command line:	sudo reboot


?.1	Webcam - Driver Installation
	- Command line:	sudo apt-get install cheese
	
